##Waiting for rework: someone really doesn't want to be at home with kids anymore

Wechat media-fox

Features, for those who insist on serious reading options. Sohu News Extreme Day studio.

ABSRTACT: Since the epidemic, the date of returning to work has been adjusted again and again. When can we go back to the office has become one of the most concerned things. Since February 10th, people have been returning to work, in some cases after a rocky journey and in others facing job cuts. After this long holiday, it feels like a lifetime ago. In any case, returning to work may be a sign that life is back on track.

Kevin Wang yi-ran

Photo and video | Lu Meng (except byline)

Editor | Wang Shan Lin Peng

Return to duty

It is hard to imagine that "normal work" will one day become a luxury aspiration, at least according to Lin Kang, a wine online operations specialist. He works for a wine chain in the north and is a second-class national wine taster. In early February, he was busy at home, ready to launch a Valentine gift box: two wine, a red and a white, specifically selected with the Cupid LOGO winery.

Only to return to work the first day back, Linkang can go to the company, and the sales people docking. The commission would fulfill his February wish to buy a good electric tweeter and an electric piano to learn electronic music arrangements.

Affected by the epidemic, February 10 became the first day for many people to return to work in several provinces and cities. For many, this may be a sign that life is back on track after an ever-longer holiday.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers work inside a Vintage factory in Longyuan, Chaoyang District, on February 19,2020. Image: Oriental IC

Tian Zhen, the middle-level leader of the listed company, has been tormented by working from home. Every day from 9 a.m. to 6:30 p.m. , in addition to punching a time card on a nail, she also has to wear a suit, tie and style to work -- there are no barbershops open near her home in Florida, so she has to have her wife give her a haircut by shaking out audio and video clips. "The front is like a dog chewing on it. ". Meetings, large and small, required video communication, and a few days later, Tian Zhen found a way to slack off. He shaved his beard, his clothes were neat, but the camera could not see the lower part of his body wearing only a pair of trousers.

"drifting north" for many years in Hebei Wu Tian also want to return to work as soon as possible, "really do not want to coax the child! " He works in an educational institutions, usually early and late. At first, when the holiday was extended, he was very happy, "finally, I can spend more time with my son. " On February 3, the resumption of work was delayed for another week, my son didn't start kindergarten, and every day he went out, Wu Tian and his wife took turns to comfort him, and they played with all the toys in the house, wouldn't kill a six-year-old boy's passion for swimming lessons.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Passengers wear masks at the Line 10, Beijing Subway on February 16,2020.

More worried than Wu is the 90 entrepreneurs Qi mo, he is from Wuhan, small companies close to the south China seafood market. After the "closure of the city" in Wuhan, "It was difficult to get out of the district, several projects were abandoned, and the workers could not return. " Wang Han, general manager of a real enterprise in Jinan, almost counted his days. The district where he lived had confirmed cases and was completely closed for management, seeing the company start work, some employees have been returning to work, Wang can only "remote control command" , "need to sign the document saved a pile

Early on the morning of February 10, Xu Na, a 26-year-old designer wearing a blue disposable mask, stood in front of an office building near Suzhou Street, Zhongguancun, where she and her colleagues had arranged to "come back for Lao Jin's instant-boiled mutton" years ago after the company's annual meeting, but less than half of my colleagues came back, "and it felt like a lifetime ago. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Food delivery workers under the Guomao Bridge in Beijing February 16,2020.

Xu Na had her temperature taken four times in one morning. The security guard at the entrance of the residential area is on standby 24 hours a day, with access slips; at the entrance of the office building and the property, the company name and the floor must be checked; the elevator is filled with a strong smell of disinfectant; Xu Na presses the button through a paper towel, and the support staff will check it every two hours, go to her station and take her temperature. Face Masks and vials of disinfectant have replaced the usual toiletries in her bag. "Just show your eyes, and you can stop washing your face. " Only a few people showed up for work, and the colleague sitting across from her knocked on her desk and shook her cell phone, wECHAT dialog box sent greetings: "How the year? Where to lunch? "

Not So lucky as Xu Na, Yang Lika in the office door. She and three colleagues on the way to the company, Office Building in the central area of Heping District Cbd, Tianjin, to the gate, the security guard looked at the temperature gun surprised asked: "How are you all high fever? " "May be the air conditioning on the car! " Toss about 20 minutes, rechecked several times, body temperature was normal, was put upstairs. The next day, a community near the employee's home was found to have a confirmed case, the company leader decided to continue to work from home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A security guard checks the personal information of a visitor outside the Ziguang building in Haidian District, on February 17,2020.

Rincon's been working online for a week. The company requires daily log writing, but offline sales basic no work to do, especially in charge of catering hotels and other major customers of the sales staff, at the end of the day, a sales staff on the log to hold out two: 1. I went to the client's office today. It's closed. 2. Waiting for a group assignment. The next day's log book was almost identical: 1. I went to the client's office today. It's not open. 2. Waiting for a group assignment.

On the morning of February 10, when he returned to work, Lin Kang woke up to go to work. Before his hair was shaved, he pushed the pusher neatly and neatly, and the "gas mask" was ready. But when he picked up the phone, he found a message from HR in the group, a "stand-by notice" for almost everyone:

Return to work date to be determined, before the return to work pay only 70% of the local minimum wage standard.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Beijing Haidian District, Feb. 17,2020, after the factory village, a number of Internet companies have resumed work, the picture is wearing masks exchange park staff.

You'RE GONNA get fired if this keeps up

After being laid off, they asked each person to write a work plan for the year. Linkang at home stuffy, no ideas, wearing a "gas mask" to throw garbage, want to breathe. This is the previous two years when the smog, Lin Kang bought protective products, at the time felt that "some fuss made a big deal" , after the epidemic, out of masks, masks come in handy. "Valentine's Day plan" down the drain, Lin Kang looked at the poster has been made, some lost, and the evening and lovers video, he was afraid that the other side worry: "I can save for two months. "

Rincon has been away from his lover for almost a month. Lovers engaged in construction projects, the original plan February 3 from Shenyang back to Beijing, ticket booking several times, but the company's protective supplies are insufficient, the construction site can not start, only refund.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As the epidemic spread, masks for smoggy days became a lifeline for many office workers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
To be safe, some office workers clean the floor with disinfectant every day.

There are also people out on the complicated certification and official seal "dissuade. ". Zhang Mingjia, a male student from Guangxi, lives in Nanning, the company is adjacent to the district. After the district is closed to the public, the returning workers are required to provide copies of the approval documents for the resumption of work in the enterprise Complete the formalities back to the community to fill in the permit application form, and then by the Neighborhood Committee and Health Committee audit seal, write personal commitment, before the city government audit issued a pass. Toss about a circle, finally failed, the community reply him, the company belongs to self-employed business, not in the scope of resumption.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 20,2020, express delivery center in Shanxi, the resumption of workers began to work. China Express Shanxi Provincial Management Center in the case of prevention and control of the epidemic, encourage employees to return to work in batches. Image: Oriental IC

Zhou Shang in Yongjia County, Wenzhou, may be more anxious than he is. His home town of Qiaotou, where a man had been diagnosed, was heavily guarded and closed to travel. Colleagues have been working since the 10th, Zhou Shang became the only Home Office operations specialist. In order to prove himself and everyone, not at home lazy, he even eat a computer in the next photo, "than to go to work is also tired. ". He worries, "you could get fired if you go on like this. "

The road back to business is not so easy. Qian Juan, an owner of small and medium enterprises, began buying masks and disinfectant products for employees on various e commerce platforms on New Year's Eve. She ended up buying only two packs of disposable masks and bottles of 84 disinfectant, and began contacting wechat merchants again. "without proper protection, we don't dare to put people at risk. We lose almost 300,000 yuan a month in hard spending if we don't start work. "

The profit-making departments of a state-owned enterprise are all labor-intensive industries. Xu Jia, an employee in the human resources department, said that 10,000 masks have yet to be shipped from the purchased protective products, and the factory is now simply afraid to resume work. "Our branch is aiming for 80m this year, so we have more than 10 months to go, and it will all affect our performance. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A protective clothing factory in Beijing has been back to work since the fourth day of the Lunar New Year. An employee inspects a protective suit at a production workshop on February 11,2020.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers work on a protective clothing sewing line on Feb. 11,2020.

Under pressure, many enterprises did not survive the spring. On February 10, the news that "new wave media group announced 500 job cuts" went viral.

Linkang's offline stores have been closed for more than 20 days, January salary can not come out, employees in the group "ask for salary" , Financial Comfort: "We wait. " Later, the company's sales staff and interns have received the resignation calls.

The company has divided its employees into four groups: The first group is the company's property, water and electricity, the normal salary when the shift is on duty, the rest of the time calculate leave, there is no salary; the second group is those responsible for the online business in Rinco, from 10 February until the resumption of work, only 70 per cent of the local minimum wage, or about $1,000, is paid; the third category is online business personnel who are unable to return to work on time in the field and do not receive any salary before the resumption of work; The fourth category is laid-off employees, mostly interns and sales people who don't have formal contracts and work on commission. Because these employees do not have employment contract, can only hand over the work waiting for the month's salary settlement.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A worker eats lunch in the canteen of a company that has resumed work in Shenyang, Liaoning Province, on February 19,2020. Image: Oriental IC

Life and change

A week later, on the second Monday of February 17, more people were returning to work. After 8:00 am, the whole floor of Beijing Shangpin discount commercial building was covered by a long line of people wearing masks, more than 100 meters in the cold wind waiting to register the temperature; The middle-level leader of an Internet company had his temperature taken seven times in one morning. His colleagues took off their masks while drinking coffee. After only one minute, he was caught by the property management. The administrative staff reminded him in an all-staff email, "wearing a mask during an outbreak is a rite of passage! "

For Lin Kang, this Monday is still unemployed. In the week of Feb. 3, he also sold tens of thousands of orders, including more than 20,000 LAFITE, "the rich mind is unpredictable, this time to buy wine is to sterilize the home? "

Receive"wait for a post notice"hind, the order is complete zero, he can do this year only at home"work plan"PPT.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Since returning to Beijing on February 3, employees of an Internet company in Houchang village have been working from home. Working Online is no easier than sitting at a desk, almost 24 hours a day, even on weekends.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Back to work dates have been pushed back, in addition to busy work, most of the people working from home to cook their own meals, washing dishes, some people began to miss leaving home, to the company's Normal Work Day, "a little miss the company canteen. "

He had planned to quit his job in the second half of the year or so, start a business with friends, and work as a gaming-related social platform. But when his company couldn't get back to work, when minimum wage couldn't guarantee it, when his friends'projects were put on hold, everything went haywire.

Lin Kang is more than 1.7 meters, weighing more than 200 pounds, suffering from diabetes. "We are still far away from the virus, " Lin Kang encouraged his lover, who caught a cold in Shenyang in early February and was afraid to go to the hospital. But on his third day at home, Lin Kang learned that a diabetic friend had died of new coronary pneumonia, "It was a very scary time, " he said. "It felt like it was about everyone. "

After that, linkang devoted himself to live broadcasting thoroughly, turned on the camera as soon as he woke up every day, and made more than 100 yuan a week. Live content to daily life-based, painting, dancing, hot shake music, playing games, listening to music, rolling in bed, but also "mastered a variety of new skills" : the first time cook their own food, coke wings and honey juice chicken wings, "count two dishes? "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In addition to the news, play games, painting, cooking, these usually flawless hobbies have been a lot of people back.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Staring at a still life at home when there is nothing to do has become the norm for many in the epidemic.

Sometimes Lin Kang didn't move for half a day. Fans asked him, "what's on? "

"Live Broadcast Daze Ah. " Lin Kang said, "a lot of people at home have nothing to do, what you do have people watching. "

After a long wait, the Yiwu International Trade City finally opened, the Hengdian World Studios has announced that the production team will resume work in phases, Haidilao has resumed its delivery service, and 29 beauty salons in Beijing have opened, but ask the barber not to talk to customers. A restaurant selling dumpling wontons opened its doors for a morning trial. People were wearing masks, one or two people apart. "Did you wear masks when you cut the stuffing? " One customer asked the chef cautiously

As of February 17, about 50,000 enterprises have resumed work in the CBD functional area of Beijing, accounting for more than 90% of the total number of enterprises; business buildings in Tianhe District of Guangzhou have resumed production almost 100% .

Rework Engineer Li Xian from Tianjin rented a house in Beiyuan, afraid of the highway closure, back before the 15th of the first month. The car line all the way unimpeded, Li Xian staring out the window, the street people thin, traffic sharply reduced, in the past trunk is to eat, this year are able to gather the disinfection protective supplies. Li Xian parked his car and took a rest downstairs.

"I suddenly missed Beijing, which was very crowded and very popular. "
